<div class="lg:grid lg:grid-cols-3 lg:gap-8">
  <div class="lg:col-span-2">
    <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 tracking-tight">Age Calculator</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8 leading-relaxed">Enter your birth date to instantly see your exact age in years, months, days, total days, and when your next birthday falls.</p>

    <%# Ad: leaderboard — placed below content heading per AdSense best practices %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "leaderboard" %></div>

    <div data-controller="age-calculator ad-engagement" class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-900 rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200/80 dark:border-gray-800 p-6 md:p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 md:gap-8">
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div>
            <label for="age-birth-date" class="block text-sm font-semibold text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mb-1.5">Birth Date</label>
            <input id="age-birth-date" type="date" data-age-calculator-target="birthDate" data-action="input->age-calculator#calculate" class="w-full">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true" class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 dark:from-blue-900/20 dark:to-indigo-900/20 rounded-2xl p-6">
          <h2 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-5">Results</h2>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Years</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-age-calculator-target="resultYears">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Months</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-age-calculator-target="resultMonths">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Days</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-age-calculator-target="resultDays">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Total Days</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-age-calculator-target="resultTotalDays">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
              <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Next Birthday</span>
              <span class="text-xl font-bold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400" data-age-calculator-target="resultNextBirthday">&mdash;</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <button data-action="click->age-calculator#copy" class="mt-6 w-full px-4 py-2.5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-600 to-indigo-600 hover:from-blue-700 hover:to-indigo-700 text-white rounded-xl shadow-sm shadow-blue-500/20 hover:shadow-md hover:shadow-blue-500/25 transition-all duration-200 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500 focus:ring-offset-2 text-sm font-medium">Copy Results</button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <%= render "shared/calculator_rating", slug: "age" %>
    <div class="mb-8"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_results" %></div>

    <article class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
      <h2>How to Use the Age Calculator</h2>
      <p>
        Simply select your date of birth using the date picker above. The calculator instantly determines your exact age broken down into years, months, and days. It also shows your total age in days and the date of your next birthday, which is useful for countdowns, milestone planning, or satisfying simple curiosity.
      </p>
      <p>
        The calculation accounts for the varying number of days in each month and correctly handles leap years. Whether you were born in February of a leap year or at the end of a 31-day month, the results are accurate to the day. The next birthday field updates automatically based on whether this year's birthday has already passed.
      </p>

      <div class="my-6"><%= render "shared/ad_slot", slot: "in_content" %></div>

      <h2>How Age Calculation Works</h2>
      <p>
        Age in years is determined by counting the number of complete birthdays that have passed since the birth date. The remaining months count how many complete months have elapsed since the last birthday. The remaining days count the number of days since the last complete month. For total days, the calculator computes the difference between today and the birth date as an absolute number of days, accounting for every leap year in between.
      </p>

      <h3>Leap Year Considerations</h3>
      <p>
        A leap year occurs every four years, adding February 29 to the calendar. However, years divisible by 100 are not leap years unless they are also divisible by 400. This means 2000 was a leap year, but 1900 was not. The calculator handles all these rules correctly. If you were born on February 29, your age increments on March 1 in non-leap years for the purpose of this calculation.
      </p>

      <h3>Fun Age Facts</h3>
      <p>
        At approximately 1 billion seconds old, you are about 31 years and 8 months old. The average human lifespan is roughly 27,375 days (about 75 years). A person who lives to 80 will experience approximately 20 leap days during their lifetime. Knowing your age in days can provide a unique perspective on how much time has passed and how you choose to spend the days ahead.
      </p>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <h3>How do I calculate my exact age?</h3>
      <p>
        Subtract your birth date from today's date. The result gives your age in complete years, remaining months, and remaining days. For example, if you were born on March 15, 1990, and today is April 4, 2026, you are 36 years, 0 months, and 20 days old.
      </p>

      <h3>How many days old am I?</h3>
      <p>
        Count the total number of days from your birth date to today. Our calculator does this instantly, accounting for leap years and varying month lengths. For example, someone born on January 1, 2000, would be approximately 9,590 days old on April 4, 2026.
      </p>

      <h3>When is my next birthday?</h3>
      <p>
        Your next birthday is the next occurrence of your birth month and day. If your birthday has already passed this year, the next one falls in the following year. Our calculator shows the exact date and how many days until your next birthday.
      </p>

      <h3>Does the calculator account for leap years?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes, the calculator fully accounts for leap years when computing total days and age breakdowns. Leap years add one extra day (February 29) every four years, with exceptions for years divisible by 100 unless also divisible by 400.
      </p>

      <h3>How is age calculated for legal purposes?</h3>
      <p>
        In most jurisdictions, you legally turn a year older on your birthday. For people born on February 29 (leap day), legal age milestones are typically recognized on March 1 in non-leap years. Specific rules vary by country and context, so check local regulations for official age determinations.
      </p>
    

